recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 180Â°C. Line 2 baking trays with baking paper.
Beat butter and sugar until pale and creamy. Add milk and vanilla and beat until combined. Sift flour and custard over butter mixture. Using a metal spoon, stir in until well combined.
Roll tablespoons of mixture into balls. Place onto prepared baking trays, leaving 5cm between for spreading. Press dough with floured fork. Bake for 20 minutes or until light golden.
Stand on trays before transferring to a wire rack to cool.
